                  <msItem>
                     <p> MIDELTON. <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>John</forename> 
                  le <surname>Yong</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_103277">Midelton</placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> de <surname>Linlay</surname> de <placeName role="person" key="place_103377">Thorp on the Hill</placeName>
                        </persName> 
                  and <persName>
                           <forename>Alice</forename> his wife</persName> one assart which is called 
                  <placeName type="minor">le Serlerode</placeName> in <placeName key="place_103277">Midelton</placeName>. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1300" notAfter="1310" precision="low">c. 1300-10</origDate>.) 
                  (The <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> de <surname>Fenton</surname>
                        </persName> of the next charter 
                  is a witness here, and <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> de <surname>Olton</surname>
                        </persName> witnesses both.)
                  . </p>
